title: For Sale:  Beretta 92 9mm original series 1 one  collectors
postcontent: Sorry if you tried emailing, yahoo sent it to the junk bulk folder but I am now checking that folder. It comes with the original box and 3 mags. This is an old first series model 92 that had the later straight slide in stead of the even earlier step side. Production on these stopped in 1983 and the mag release was moved closer to the trigger guard and the safety moved from the frame to the slide. It is very much not a 92fs, though the 92fs had great improvements this is more of a collectors gun. Gun shoots fairly accurate and is reliable as all those Berettas are. This is from wikepedia "Production began in May 1976, and ended in February 1983. Approximately 7,000 units were of the first "step slide" design and the rest were of the second "straight slide" type. The total production of both designs was 52,000 pistols." Sorry no trades, if you live in Carson City or Reno let me know, I make it around northern Nevada a lot. Must be 21 and have Nevada drivers license. Gun is in 9mm parabellum (luger) obviously. Those of you who know and shoot Axion products know of their amazing quality and durability. 5 pins in .020 size. There is also an adjustable Axion rheostat blue light added to the sight. The light mounts in the bracket of the sight, so that it shines only on the extended fibers of the pins. Very few rests have this function as most other models reset when the bow is drawn. This rest will not drop away until the bow has been shot.
